Command:
git commit -m "perf(ft-api): parallelize histogramdd local counts" ...

Result:
The repository pre-commit hook invoked UBS on the staged files and detected
`crates/ft-api/src/lib.rs` as a large staged file. It ran with the hook's
extended timeout, then exited nonzero with:

ubs: timeout on large file scan
ubs: run manually: ubs --only=rust crates/ft-api/src/lib.rs
ubs: or commit with: UBS_SKIP=1 git commit ...

Follow-up:
Manual two-file UBS for `crates/ft-api/src/lib.rs` and
`crates/ft-api/benches/ops_bench.rs` had already remained silent in the Rust
module for about five minutes and was terminated; see
`pass6_ubs_ft_api_changed_files.log`.

Commit decision:
Use `UBS_SKIP=1` for this commit because the scanner timed out twice on the
large `ft-api/src/lib.rs` surface, while RCH focused behavior proof, same-worker
benchmark, `cargo check -p ft-api --all-targets`, and cached whitespace checks
completed and are recorded in pass1-pass7.
